value.0: James Blacksriver, this headstone proudly declares. Known as a crass and greasy fighter from the Crownlands during the Interregnum, this former Sheriff of Brost County was executed for a multitude of crimes, including corruption, theft, and assault upon a noblewoman.
Zachariah Abdelnakim, this headstone proudly declares. A man, presumed a Cyricist, who spat upon the Knighthood and who's mettle was found lacking.

This monument seems to be erected around the grave of the Liberator - Roderick Llannistaph Senior. The former baron of Lockwood Falls, the Liberator is well known for his protection of the peasantry of Brost as well as exerting his influence to try and keep the village within the domain of Tethyr when it attempted to join Amn during the Interegnum.
Parian Mendt, a druid who ritualistic suicide after disclosing druidic secrets, was buried here...Until someone or something dug his body up.

Nickolas Rand - Twice Born, Twice Blessed by Tempus was a warrior of peerless skill amongst the baronies of Brost. His power was taken from him by performing dishonorable duties in the service of his lord - earning him the nickname the "Blackguard of Brost."

Asfora el Nadim was a well-regarded Calishite mage in Brost County...That is until she and her co-conspirators were discovered attempting to destabilize the Baronies. She and her companions were executed as insurrectionists who may have had ties to the Cowled Wizards of Amn.

Lily Davis was considered one of Brost's quieter Peers. However, in truth, she and her co-conspirators were discovered attempting to usurp the authority of Queen Zaranda Star and the Office of the Justicar. Foul creations and strange ritualistic objects were found in her home, branding her as an Occultist and an enemy of all good men and women in the County.

Sir Darius Obreck was a well-known hero of Brost County. Wielding a holy great sword of Torm and golden armor with bright red hair, he was difficult to mistake for anyone else. Sir Darius gave his life defending the people of Brost from a goblin horde, and is enshrined forever as a paragon of virtue and valor - an example to all Knights of Tethyr!

Sir Andrew Skyraven was a knight of Siamorphe and Tethyr who was as honorable in life as he was in death - he gave his life defending the people of Brost from a goblin assault on West Haven, proving that his valor and honor were worthy of his station.

Sir Lucas Remmington was both the Magistrate of Brost and then Her Majesty's eigth official appointment as Justicar for the Sword Belt. He served the Crown and Tethyr as an Inquisitor and Blackcoat with honor and valor - ensuring that those within Brost County were able to live in peace without fear of intrigues from within or without.

Hammond Harrington was a Lathanderite known for his service as a deputy Magistrate. Afterwards, he became more nomadic. More than once he declared his allegiance for a Lord, until one finally decided to award him with the charge of dissertion that lost him his head.
Aimee Leonson, this grave declares...With no accompanying information.

Value.value: Fog nips at your heels as you move forward on this path.  An idol stands in the center of a sea of pale tombstones.
